ll/281.patch', 'issue_url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/spring-projects/spring-retry/issues/281', 'number': 281, 'state': 'open', 'locked': False, 'title': 'Rethrow particular not-retryable exceptions', 'user': {'login': 'ttulka', 'id': 7925050, 'node_id': 'MDQ6VXNlcjc5MjUwNTA=', 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/7925050?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/ttulka', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/ttulka', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/ttulka/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/ttulka/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/ttulka/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/ttulka/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/ttulka/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/ttulka/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/ttulka/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/ttulka/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/ttulka/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}, 'body': 'Although `rethrow` helps a lot I have use-cases where I need exception handling to be even more flexible.

- Rethrow particular not-retryable exceptions without recovering and wrapping them: `rethrowExceptions`

**Example:**
I want to retry server exceptions except for an authorization exception as this should be sent immediately and directly to the caller. 

```java
@Retry(include={ServerException.class}, rethrowExceptions={AuthorizationException.class})
public String makeSomeCall() { … }

@Recover
private String recoverThatCall(Throwable t) {
    // not for AuthorizationException
}
```
