You mean for all not-retryable exceptions, right? Retryable exceptions should always go to the recovery method, even with `rethrow=true`.

So, if I understand you correctly, you want `include` exceptions to be retried, `rethrowable` exceptions to be rethrown without modification, skipping any matching recovery method, and any not listed exceptions to go straight to the recovery method, if one matches, and rethrown without modification if no recovery method matches?

If so, we would have to clearly document that in the README and javadocs.

I really think the `@Recover` annotation is complicated enough already but; I still think we should try to achieve your use case some other way. Need to think some more.

